<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-451-233  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 451 233.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Sept 3 1990 v7 n10 p44(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The LAN administrator. (local area networks)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Liebing, Edward.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many companies have not defined the differences between the localarea network (LAN) administrator and the MIS manager.andP;  The jobdescriptions of each should clearly define the responsibilities ofeach job.andP;  Also, the LAN administrator's role in the company'smanagement structure should be defined.andP;  The LAN administrator isresponsible for protecting the hardware, software, and dataassets; keeping costs down; coordinating with other departmentsand central MIS on access to data bases; coordinating with otherdepartments and MIS on purchasing; keeping the computer up andrunning; and ensuring information reliability.andP;  A major area ofcontention between LAN administrators and MIS is who can make abuying decision, with MIS saying it should be centralized and LANadministrators saying MIS does not have enough knowledge about LANneeds to make an intelligent purchasing decision.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksMISNetwork Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>